Here is a good blog entry about Object-oriented Programming (OOP) [What Is Object-Oriented Programming][2]



    class Snake:
       name = &#39;Python&#39;
       snake1 = Snake()
       snake2 = Snake()

       snake1.name = &quot;Carl&quot;
       snake2.name = &quot;Hans&quot;
       print(snake1.name)
       print(snake2.name)
       print(Snake.name)
       //Output 
