By using `&lt;?php echo json_encode($nick); ?&gt;` in `1.php` you are recoursing back to PHP which is not useful except you submit the entire `1.php` file back to the server for PHP preprocessing.

Remember, you have already retrieved the data of `2.php` via ajax. You can store that data in a global variable so it is accessible to the entire `1.php`. 


This is a recast of `1.php`

